# Build context for the repo ROOT — used only by tests/Dockerfile (the cross-container test-runner).
# `web/` and `ai/` build from their own contexts and keep their own .dockerignore.
#
# Keeps the runner's context small and, above all, keeps SECRETS out of it: a `.env` copied into an
# image layer is readable by anyone who can pull that image.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

.git/
.github/
.githooks/

__pycache__/
*.pyc
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
venv/

docs/
*.md
